{"number":"57","directions":"<p style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Exercise 57:</span></b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> Creating 10 simple displays for your light sculpture</span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">DESCRIPTION:</span></b></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">In the previous exercises we have learned all the basics that are required to program your light sculpture. Now it is time to begin making 10 simple displays that will be the starting point for your light sculpture program. Once you have those 10 simple displays, we can insert them into a template for the light sculpture program and then you will be well along in creating your own unique program for your light sculpture.</span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Ideas for your 10 simple displays could include but are not limited to:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Lighting up each Color</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Slowly lighting up each LED one at a time</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Going around / spinning</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Stair Step</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Stair Fall</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Lights chasing one another</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Lights colliding and falling back</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Lights colliding and splitting</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Lights colliding then splitting then re-combining</span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"></span></li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Requirements for your 10 simple displays</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">The combined runtime of all 10 simple displays must be at least a minute, several minutes is better.</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">The first display must be some sort of introduction (i.e. starting slow, showing off your colors or shapes).</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">The displays must build on each other (i.e. start slow, then speeding up, or perhaps start small then go bigger).  Try to make each display a little more interesting than the last.</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">The displays must be different from each other.  Going forward then backwards can be a good thing to do, but that might count only as one display.</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Each simple display MUST be a Function that uses at least three arguments(typically onTime, offTime, repeatCount).</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Each simple display MUST use loops and arrays wherever possible.</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Create all your 10 Simple Displays in One Arduino Sketch - YourInitials_10Simple in: Documents – Arduino – Exercises</span></li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p style=\"line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><b><i><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">ACTIVITIES:</span></i></b></p>\n<ol style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\">\n<li style=\"list-style-type: decimal; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Start with any code you have already written. Your completed exercise49 has functions and an array, which is as good as a starting place as any. Save it as YourInitials_10Simple in: Documents – Arduino – Exercises from the Arduino IDE</span></li>\n<li style=\"list-style-type: decimal; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Start making your 10 simple functions using the ideas and requirements outlined above.</span></li>\n<li style=\"list-style-type: decimal; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">This would be a good time to use the </span><a href=\"https://dpengineering.github.io/light-simulator/index.html\" style=\"text-decoration: none;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #1155cc; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: underline; -webkit-text-decoration-skip: none; text-decoration-skip-ink: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">3D light Sculpture Simulator</span></a><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"> to test your code. You can input your rod locations, lengths, and colors, then use the edit code button to paste in your Simple functions to test them out.</span></li>\n<li style=\"list-style-type: decimal; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">When you have finished your 10 Simple Displays, save it in Documents – Arduino – Exercises</span></li>\n<li style=\"list-style-type: decimal; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\"><i><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Go </span></i><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">to CL 10.4.27 Upload Completed Exercise57: And upload evidence that you have completed Exercise57</span></li>\n<li style=\"list-style-type: decimal; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Click \"Prepare an answer\" on NEO</span></li>\n<li style=\"list-style-type: decimal; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Copy your 10 Simple Displays code from the Arduino IDE, and paste by pressing CTRL + V</span></li>\n<li style=\"list-style-type: decimal; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Click \"Save and submit for grading\"</span></li>\n</ol>","startingCode":"//**************ACTIVITIES TO CHECK WHILE GRADING**********BEGIN*********\n//\n// 1.\tMake sure that an array named LEDsCounterClockwiseStartAt15 has been created and used\n// 2.\tEnsure that a function has been created named ArraysSequenceLEDsCounterClockwiseStartAt15\n// 3.\tThe order of the LED’s should be 15,14,13,12,11,10,9,2,3,4,5,6,7,8\n// 4.\tMake sure that function uses three parameters (example – but not required - ledOnTime, ledOffTime, and repeatCount)\n//\n// ***************ACTIVITIES TO CHECK WHILE GRADING END*********************\n\nvoid setup()\n{\n  int LEDNum;\n\n  for(LEDNum = 2; LEDNum <= 15; LEDNum++)\n  {\n    pinMode(LEDNum, OUTPUT);\n  }\n}\n\nvoid loop()\n{\n  ArraysSequenceLEDsCounterClockwiseStartAt15(100,100, 3);\n}\n\nvoid ArraysSequenceLEDsCounterClockwiseStartAt15(int onTime, int offTime, int repeatCount)\n{\n  int LEDsCounterClockwiseStartAt15[14] = {\n    15,14,13,12,11,10,9,2,3,4,5,6,7,8    };\n  int index;\n  int count;\n\n  for (count = 1; count <= repeatCount; count++)\n  {\n    for (index = 0; index <= 13; index++)\n    {\n      digitalWrite(LEDsCounterClockwiseStartAt15[index], HIGH);\n      delay(onTime);\n      digitalWrite(LEDsCounterClockwiseStartAt15[index], LOW);\n      delay(offTime);\n    }\n  }\n}\n\n","suffix":"int main() {\n  setup();\n  loop();\n  return 0;\n}\n","board":{"type":"LED Board","setup":{"pinKeyframes":[]}},"frameManager":{"frames":[{"ledModes":{},"ledStates":{},"postDelay":500,"outputText":["Hello World!","\n"]},{"ledModes":{},"ledStates":{},"postDelay":5000,"outputText":["Good Bye World!!","\n"]},{"ledModes":{},"ledStates":{},"postDelay":0,"outputText":[]}],"currentFrame":2,"elapsedTime":5500,"isGraded":true,"grade":false}}